Name: count, dtype: int64\n"]}]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["### Class Distribution\n","\n","In this step, we analyzed the distribution of the target classes in the training dataset.\n","\n","The output shows:\n","- Class 0 (World): 30,000 samples\n","- Class 1 (Sports): 30,000 samples\n","- Class 2 (Business): 30,000 samples\n","- Class 3 (Sci/Tech): 30,000 samples\n","\n","This indicates that the dataset is **perfectly balanced**, with an equal number of samples in each class.\n","\n","A balanced dataset is beneficial because:\n","- It prevents bias toward any particular class during training\n","- It allows the model to learn all categories equally well\n","- Evaluation metrics like accuracy become more reliable\n","\n","This ensures a fair comparison between different models in later stages of the assignment."],"metadata":{"id":"zcxCToVm2Yyc"}},{"cell_type":"code","source":["import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n","\n","# Plot class distribution\n","class_counts.plot(kind='bar')\n","\n","plt.title(\"Class Distribution\")\n","plt.xlabel(\"Class Label\")\n","plt.ylabel(\"Number of Samples\")\n","plt.show()"],"metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/","height":467},"id":"UeBX798R1uY0","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1777291940246,"user_tz":-330,"elapsed":995,"user":{"displayName":"Amit Kadia","userId":"00743091928818247073"}},"outputId":"188c7820-005b-4d96-883d-fdc606d98014"},"execution_count":4,"outputs":[{"output_type":"display_data","data":{"text/plain":["<Figure size 640x480 with 1 Axes>"],"image/png":"\n"},"metadata":{}}]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["### Visualization of Class Distribution\n","\n","In this step, we visualized the distribution of classes using a bar chart.\n","\n","From the plot, we can clearly observe that:\n","- All four classes (0: World, 1: Sports, 2: Business, 3: Sci/Tech) have the same number of samples.\n","- Each class contains approximately 30,000 training examples.\n","\n","This confirms that the dataset is **perfectly balanced**.\n","\n","A balanced dataset is important because:\n","- It ensures that the model does not become biased toward any specific class\n","- It allows fair learning across all categories\n","- It leads to more reliable evaluation of model performance\n","\n","This makes the AG News dataset well-suited for training and comparing different RNN-based models."],"metadata":{"id":"DFD6G-Qf25Yw"}},{"cell_type":"code","source":["# Extract text and labels\n","\n","train_texts = dataset['train']['text']\n","train_labels = dataset['train']['label']\n","\n","test_texts = dataset['test']['text']\n","test_labels = dataset['test']['label']\n","\n","# Check a sample\n","print(train_texts[0])\n","print(train_labels[0])"],"metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/"},"id":"_bF-I2ZZ1uWF","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1777292156286,"user_tz":-330,"elapsed":44,"user":{"displayName":"Amit Kadia","userId":"00743091928818247073"}},"outputId":"2d7d26ad-c054-458d-df59-daadc657b456"},"execution_count":5,"outputs":[{"output_type":"stream","name":"stdout","text":["Wall St. Bears Claw Back Into the Black (Reuters) Reuters - Short-sellers, Wall Street's dwindling\\band of ultra-cynics, are seeing green again.\n","2\n"]}]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["### Text and Label Extraction\n","\n","In this step, we extracted the text and label data from the dataset.\n","\n","- `train_texts` and `test_texts` contain the news articles\n","- `train_labels` and `test_labels` contain the corresponding category labels\n","\n","We printed one sample to verify:\n","- The text represents a news article headline and description\n","- The label is an integer value (0 to 3), where:\n","  - 0 → World\n","  - 1 → Sports\n","  - 2 → Business\n","  - 3 → Sci/Tech\n","\n","This step prepares the data for the next stage, which is tokenization, where text will be converted into numerical form suitable for deep learning models."],"metadata":{"id":"hXKz5sdq3nAs"}},{"cell_type":"code","source":["from tensorflow.keras.preprocessing.text import Tokenizer\n","\n","# Define vocabulary size\n","vocab_size = 20000\n","\n","# Initialize tokenizer\n","tokenizer = Tokenizer(num_words=vocab_size, oov_token=\"<OOV>\")\n","\n","# Fit tokenizer on training text\n","tokenizer.fit_on_texts(train_texts)\n","\n","# Convert text to sequences\n","train_sequences = tokenizer.texts_to_sequences(train_texts)\n","test_sequences = tokenizer.texts_to_sequences(test_texts)\n","\n","# Check one example\n","print(\"Original text:\\n\", train_texts[0])\n","print(\"\\nSequence:\\n\", train_sequences[0])"],"metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/"},"id":"DQS-OWGU1uTO","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1777292233285,"user_tz":-330,"elapsed":21973,"user":{"displayName":"Amit Kadia","userId":"00743091928818247073"}},"outputId":"9e454eba-2379-4b2f-f0f0-4fa87f856285"},"execution_count":6,"outputs":[{"output_type":"stream","name":"stdout","text":["Original text:\n"," Wall St. Bears Claw Back Into the Black (Reuters) Reuters - Short-sellers, Wall Street's dwindling\\band of ultra-cynics, are seeing green again.\n","\n","Sequence:\n"," [443, 442, 1682, 14529, 109, 65, 2, 851, 22, 22, 754, 8197, 443, 6641, 10232, 2928, 5, 5811, 1, 41, 4050, 798, 333]\n"]}]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["### Tokenization\n","\n","In this step, we converted text data into numerical format using a tokenizer.\n","\n","- We defined a vocabulary size of 20,000 words.\n","- The tokenizer was fitted on the training text to build a word index.\n","- Each unique word is assigned an integer index based on its frequency.\n","\n","After tokenization:\n","- The original text is transformed into a sequence of integers.\n","- Each number represents a specific word from the vocabulary.\n","\n","We also used an `<OOV>` (Out Of Vocabulary) token:\n","- This handles words that are not present in the top 20,000 most frequent words.\n","- Such words are mapped to a special token to avoid errors during inference.\n","\n","This step is essential because neural networks cannot process raw text directly. Tokenization converts textual data into a numerical representation that models can understand."],"metadata":{"id":"qaD_h7xc4Bhg"}},{"cell_type":"code","source":["from tensorflow.keras.preprocessing.sequence import pad_sequences\n","\n","# Define max length\n","max_length = 100\n","\n","# Apply padding\n","train_padded = pad_sequences(train_sequences, maxlen=max_length, padding='post', truncating='post')\n","test_padded = pad_sequences(test_sequences, maxlen=max_length, padding='post', truncating='post')\n","\n","# Check shape\n","print(\"Train padded shape:\", train_padded.shape)\n","print(\"Test padded shape:\", test_padded.shape)"],"metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/"},"id":"7AxFJdIY1uQe","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1777292317891,"user_tz":-330,"elapsed":651,"user":{"displayName":"Amit Kadia","userId":"00743091928818247073"}},"outputId":"39c70c49-397d-46a4-a105-3ca6d841192b"},"execution_count":7,"outputs":[{"output_type":"stream","name":"stdout","text":["Train padded shape: (120000, 100)\n","Test padded shape: (7600, 100)\n"]}]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["### Padding Sequences\n","\n","In this step, we applied padding to ensure that all input sequences have the same length.\n","\n","- We set a fixed maximum sequence length of 100.\n","- Sequences shorter than 100 are padded with zeros at the end (`padding='post'`).\n","- Sequences longer than 100 are truncated from the end (`truncating='post'`).\n","\n","After padding:\n","- Training data shape: (120000, 100)\n","- Test data shape: (7600, 100)\n","\n","Padding is important because:\n","- Neural networks require inputs of uniform size\n","- It ensures efficient batch processing\n","- It prevents shape mismatch errors during model training\n","\n","Now, all text data is converted into fixed-length numerical sequences, making it ready for model training."],"metadata":{"id":"bei8mMC94Rzv"}},{"cell_type":"code","source":["  from tensorflow.keras.utils import to_categorical\n","\n","# Convert labels to categorical (one-hot encoding)\n","train_labels_cat = to_categorical(train_labels, num_classes=4)\n","test_labels_cat = to_categorical(test_labels, num_classes=4)\n","\n","# Check shapes\n","print(\"Train labels shape:\", train_labels_cat.shape)\n","print(\"Test labels shape:\", test_labels_cat.shape)"],"metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/"},"id":"e7Dax7-S1uNm","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1777292394583,"user_tz":-330,"elapsed":3997,"user":{"displayName":"Amit Kadia","userId":"00743091928818247073"}},"outputId":"9a8c7448-a086-4bff-9d47-6579d096a7ec"},"execution_count":8,"outputs":[{"output_type":"stream","name":"stdout","text":["Train labels shape: (120000, 4)\n","Test labels shape: (7600, 4)\n"]}]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["### Label Encoding\n","\n","In this step, we converted the labels into one-hot encoded format using `to_categorical`.\n","\n","- Original labels were integers (0 to 3), representing the four categories.\n","- After encoding, each label is represented as a vector of length 4.\n","\n","For example:\n","- Class 0 → [1, 0, 0, 0]\n","- Class 1 → [0, 1, 0, 0]\n","- Class 2 → [0, 0, 1, 0]\n","- Class 3 → [0, 0, 0, 1]\n","\n","After conversion:\n","- Training labels shape: (120000, 4)\n","- Test labels shape: (7600, 4)\n","\n","One-hot encoding is necessary because:\n","- The model uses **softmax activation** in the output layer\n","- The loss function (categorical crossentropy) expects labels in this format\n","\n","Now, both input data and labels are fully prepared for training RNN-based models."],"metadata":{"id":"LoOWCxpl4iE6"}},{"cell_type":"code","source":["from tensorflow.keras.models import Sequential\n","from tensorflow.keras.layers import Embedding, SimpleRNN, Dense\n","\n","# Build model\n","model = Sequential([\n","    Embedding(input_dim=vocab_size