":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1777299374628,"user_tz":-330,"elapsed":47,"user":{"displayName":"Amit Kadia","userId":"00743091928818247073"}},"outputId":"17c48c7d-ebbf-4782-d46b-11abb22e1f8f"},"execution_count":29,"outputs":[{"output_type":"stream","name":"stdout","text":["        Model  Training Accuracy  Validation Accuracy  Test Accuracy\n","0  Simple RNN             0.2866               0.3049         0.2972\n","1        LSTM             0.9388               0.9032         0.9117\n","2         GRU             0.9611               0.8967         0.9101\n","3     Bi-LSTM             0.9720               0.8940         0.9071\n"]}]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["### Comparison of RNN-Based Models\n","\n","In this step, we compared the performance of different RNN-based models.\n","\n","| Model       | Training Accuracy | Validation Accuracy | Test Accuracy |\n","|------------|------------------|--------------------|--------------|\n","| Simple RNN | 0.2866           | 0.3049             | 0.2972       |\n","| LSTM       | 0.9388           | 0.9032             | 0.9117       |\n","| GRU        | 0.9611           | 0.8967             | 0.9101       |\n","| Bi-LSTM    | 0.9720           | 0.8940             | 0.9071       |\n","\n","#### Observations:\n","- Simple RNN performs poorly (~30% accuracy), close to random guessing.\n","- LSTM significantly improves performance (~91% test accuracy).\n","- GRU achieves similar performance to LSTM with slightly higher training accuracy.\n","- Bi-LSTM has the highest training accuracy but slightly lower test accuracy.\n","\n","#### Key Insights:\n","- LSTM and GRU are much more effective than Simple RNN.\n","- GRU is more efficient with comparable performance.\n","- Bi-LSTM captures more context but does not significantly outperform LSTM.\n","\n","#### Conclusion:\n","- LSTM provides the best balance between performance and stability.\n","- GRU is a strong alternative with lower computational cost.\n","- Simple RNN is not suitable for complex text classification tasks."],"metadata":{"id":"FwOHwDy7TO2q"}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["### Final Conclusion\n","\n","1. **Which model achieved the best test accuracy?**  \n","   The LSTM model achieved the best test accuracy (91.17%), closely followed by GRU (~91.01%).\n","\n","2. **How did Simple RNN compare with LSTM and GRU?**  \n","   The Simple RNN performed poorly (29.72% accuracy) compared to LSTM and GRU (~91%). This shows that Simple RNN is not effective for capturing long-term dependencies in text data.\n","\n","3. **Did Bi-LSTM improve classification performance?**  \n","   Bi-LSTM did not significantly improve performance. Although it achieved higher training accuracy, its test accuracy (~90.71%) was slightly lower than LSTM.\n","\n","4. **Did gradient clipping make training more stable?**  \n","   Gradient clipping did not significantly change performance, as the model was already stable. However, it slightly improved training smoothness and is useful for preventing exploding gradients in more complex models.\n","\n","5. **Which model would you choose for this dataset and why?**  \n","   The LSTM model is the best choice because it provides the highest test accuracy with stable training behavior. GRU is also a good alternative due to its efficiency and comparable performance."],"metadata":{"id":"t-0klNIpTSXf"}}],"metadata":{"colab":{"provenance":[{"file_id":"/v2/external/notebooks/intro.ipynb","timestamp":1777291370707}]},"kernelspec":{"display_name":"Python 3","name":"python3"},"widgets":{"application/vnd.jupyter.widget-state+json":{"a9153d21c8ec4d99b5ac2fc1c6935e34":{"model_module":"@jupyter-widgets/controls","model_name":"HBoxModel","model_module_version":"1.5.0","state":{"_dom_classes":[],"_model_module":"@jupyter-widgets/controls","_model_module_version":"1.5.0","_model_name":"HBoxModel","_view_count":null,"_view_module":"@jupyter-widgets/controls","_view_module_version":"1.5.0","_view_name":"HBoxView","box_style":"","